.TH HEXCALC 1 "November 2025" "hexcalc 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hexcalc \- professional hexadecimal calculator CLI tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hexcalc
[\fIOPERATION\fR] [\fIOPERANDS\fR...] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B HexCalc
is a powerful command-line tool for performing hexadecimal arithmetic
and bitwise operations with support for multiple operands and various
output formats.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS "Arithmetic Operations"
.TP
.BR \-a ", " \-\-add " " \fIHEX\fR...
Add multiple hexadecimal values
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-subtract " " \fIHEX\fR...
Subtract hexadecimal values sequentially
.TP
.BR \-m ", " \-\-multiply " " \fIHEX\fR...
Multiply multiple hexadecimal values
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-divide " " \fIHEX\fR...
Divide hexadecimal values (integer division)
.TP
.BR \-fd ", " \-\-floatDivide " " \fIHEX\fR...
Divide hexadecimal values (floating-point division)
.TP
.BR \-mod ", " \-\-modulo " " \fIHEX\fR " " \fIHEX\fR
Modulo operation
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-power " " \fIHEX\fR " " \fIHEX\fR
Power operation (base ** exponent)
.SS "Bitwise Operations"
.TP
.BR \-and ", " \-\-bitwiseAnd " " \fIHEX\fR...
Bitwise AND operation
.TP
.BR \-or ", " \-\-bitwiseOr " " \fIHEX\fR...
Bitwise OR operation
.TP
.BR \-xor ", " \-\-bitwiseXor " " \fIHEX\fR...
Bitwise XOR operation
.TP
.BR \-not ", " \-\-bitwiseNot " " \fIHEX\fR
Bitwise NOT operation
.TP
.BR \-ls ", " \-\-leftShift " " \fIHEX\fR " " \fIPOS\fR
Left shift operation
.TP
.BR \-rs ", " \-\-rightShift " " \fIHEX\fR " " \fIPOS\fR
Right shift operation
.SS "Output Options"
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-format " " {hex,dec,bin,oct,all}
Output format (default: hex)
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Show verbose output with operation details
.TP
.BR \-bits ", " \-\-bitWidth " " \fIN\fR
Bit width for NOT operation (default: 64)
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help message and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show version information and exit
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Addition with multiple operands:
.B hexcalc \-a 0x100 0xFF 0x50
.TP
Subtraction:
.B hexcalc \-s 0x5bbcfd38e33d 0x96
.TP
Bitwise AND:
.B hexcalc \-and 0xFF 0x0F
.TP
Show all formats:
.B hexcalc \-a 0x10 0x20 \-f all
